snippet.textDisplay: I love this song; I listen to it over and over!  I envisage my upcoming marriage.  I am undergoing a terrible (horrendous) divorce having accidentally (unknowingly) married a witch whore; Allah finally is getting me nijaadh, and I am seeking to get married again very soon In Shah Allah.  I just have the remaining task of getting my son, Ardavan Syed's legal / physical custody from that whore.  I wasn't so happy 3 years back in comparison to now when I just hear this song.  I can almost feel the crisp Sherwani, and the fragrance of flower garlands, sehra, etc.  This son really puts me in the mood for passion, romance, etc.  Only Pakistan can produce such a beautiful song with its rich cultural heritage.
